The paper presents a new demand-driven pointer analysis for C programs that is designed to work efficiently in environments with small time and memory budgets such as IDEs. The paper focuses on the implementation and evaluation of the proposed analysis, and does not introduce any new theoretical concepts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages), which is concerned with the design, implementation, and analysis of programming languages and their associated tools. Other likely categories include cs.SE (Software Engineering), which is concerned with the development and maintenance of software systems, cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is concerned with the development of algorithms and models that can learn from data, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), which is concerned with the design and analysis of secure systems, and cs.SY (Systems and Control), which is concerned with the design and analysis of complex systems.
